				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Interrupting a instruction could have disastrous results. The way the CPU works is that it only checks for interrupts when instructions finish, so even if the IRQ signal is asserted in the middle of an instruction, the CPU will only notice it when the instruction ends.</div>

