				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">CPUs that abandons the current multi-cycle instruction to service interrupts are not common. ARM can do this, at least the Cortex-M profile. In fact, there are three silicon options available: do not interrupt instructions, interrupt multi-cycle instructions but the instruction will be completely re-executed, interrupt multi-cycle instructions and save enough state on the stack to resume it. The 2nd variant is the most common.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />((λ (x) (x x)) (λ (x) (x x)))</div>
